<lesson>
    <slide>
        <text name="text">
            "Great job! You made a real app with a question. But it’s not fun when there’s only one question, right?"
        </text>
        <image name="image">"slide_8_1_friendship_test"</image>
        <image name="image">"slide_8_1_trivia_master"</image>
        <image name="image">"slide_8_1_flash_cards"</image>
    </slide>

    <slide>
        <text name="text">
            "To add more questions, you can repeat the entire process you went through. In this lesson we’ll recall what exactly did we do and highlight some important points."
        </text>
        <image name="imageSource">"slide_4_1a_friendship_test"</image>
        <image name="imageSource">"slide_4_1a_trivia_master"</image>
        <image name="imageSource">"slide_4_1a_flash_cards"</image>
    </slide>

    <slide>
        <text name="text">
            "In the Design screen we’ll add a Text element for every question and a Button for every answer. Every element’s ID should be unique, but if many elements have a similar role, we can give them the same name prefix and a different number."
        </text>
        <image name="image">"slide_8_3"</image>
    </slide>

    <slide>
        <text name="text">
            "In the Code screen we’ll create a function for every question, in which we’ll write the code that gives the button a name, and changes its text to the answer. The name of the function should also be unique."
        </text>
        <image name="image">"slide_7_5"</image>
    </slide>

    <slide>
        <text name="text">
            "Back in the Design screen, we’ll define each button’s onClick property to be its appropriate function."
        </text>
        <image name="image">"slide_8_5"</image>
    </slide>

    <slide>
        <text name="text">
            "In order to keep things in order, we should pick a number for every question and name the functions and IDs accordingly."
        </text>
        <image name="image">"slide_8_6"</image>
    </slide>

    <slide>
        <text name="text">
            "It’s best to issue meaningful names."
        </text>
        <image name="image">"slide_8_7"</image>
    </slide>


    <exercise>
